<item>
            <title>[FELIX-5223] [IE11][Edge]: Fields in OSGI Configuration Manager are not editable</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/FELIX-5223</link>
                <project id="12310100" key="FELIX">Felix</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Access the configuration manager (/system/console/configMgr) using IE11 or Microsoft Edge.&lt;br/&gt;
Find a configuration that allows the user to input text inside a textfield. The content of these fields is not visible or editable because the height of the field is set to 0px. &lt;br/&gt;
Investigation seems to point to a malfunction of the autosize JS library, as this line in config.js set the height to 0:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;+        $(textareaEl).autosize(); &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;A possible solution would be to set a min-height on the textfields, if the issue in the library isn&apos;t fixed.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
